options.content:
# Useful Information
[IDCEvo Wiki: Add new elements into Grafana](https://asc.bmwgroup.net/wiki/display/IDCEVO/4.12%29+Add+new+elements+into+Grafana)\
[Grafana Documentation](https://grafana.com/docs/grafana/latest/panels-visualizations/)

For this dashboard, there's a time filter activated for every kpi. If a given kpi has not been published within a certain time range, the panel corresponding to that kpi will not be shown.

# [RESET Dashboard vars](https://mgu-gen22-si-metrics.bmwgroup.net/grafana/d/HeSAainNz/traas-versus-farm-generic-performance-kpi-reboots?orgId=1)
You probably need to refresh the page after click here

targets.query: SELECT "job", "build_url", "release","hardware_revision", "hardware_variant", "build", "branch", "job_timestamp" FROM "job_duration" WHERE ("hardware_revision" =~ /^$hardware_revision$/) AND ("job" =~ /^$job_name$/) AND ("release" =~ /^$release$/) AND $timeFilter

panels.description: This graph displays the statistics of KPI: *$kpi_name*, collected during job execution of [$job_name](https://cc-ci.bmwgroup.net/zuul/t/idcevo/builds?job_name=$job_name). This job is responsible for running a [test](https://cc-github.bmwgroup.net/idcevo/si-test-idcevo/blob/master/si_test_idcevo/si_test_package_kpi_reboots/systemtests/multiple_reboots_kpi_tests.py#L67-L173) which reboots the target a predefined number of times, collects the desired KPIs, and sends them to InfluxDB. Each KPI is collected a '**count**' number of times per job execution, and the terms *max_per_job*, *mean_per_job*, and *min_per_job* represent the maximum, mean, and minimum value of the set of values taken by kpi: *$kpi_name*, per job execution.

targets.query: SELECT mean  FROM "generic_kpi_time_value_stats" WHERE ("kpi_name" =~ /^$kpi_name$/) AND ("job" =~ /^$job_name$/) AND ("build" =~ /^$build_id$/) AND ("hardware_revision" =~ /^$hardware_revision$/) AND ("release" =~ /^$release$/) AND $timeFilter GROUP BY "job"
SELECT "value" FROM   /generic_kpi_metric_threshold.*/

This job is responsible for running a [test](https://cc-github.bmwgroup.net/idcevo/si-test-idcevo/blob/master/si_test_idcevo/si_test_package_kpi_reboots/systemtests/multiple_reboots_kpi_tests.py#L67-L173) which reboots the target a predefined number of times, collects the desired KPIs, and sends them to InfluxDB. Each KPI is collected a '**count**' number of times per job execution, and the terms *max_per_job*, *mean_per_job*, and *min_per_job* represent the maximum, mean, and minimum value of the set of values taken by kpi: *$kpi_name*, per job execution.

targets.query: SELECT mean  FROM "generic_kpi_time_value_stats" WHERE ("kpi_name" =~ /^$kpi_name$/) AND ("job" =~ /^$job_name$/) AND ("build" =~ /^$build_id$/) AND ("hardware_revision" =~ /^$hardware_revision$/) AND ("release" =~ /^$release$/) AND $timeFilter GROUP BY "job"
SELECT "value" FROM   /generic_kpi_metric_threshold.*/
